      <head>Paul Müller (Professor)</head>
      <div>

        <p>Father of Schenker pupil <ref cRef="entity-000618">Siegfried Fritz Müller</ref>.</p>

        <p>Paul Müller was married to Olga (1867–), the sister of <ref cRef="entity-000119"
            >Friedrich Siegfried Buxbaum</ref> (principal cellist of the Vienna Symphony Orchestra
          and cellist of the <ref cRef="entity-000727">Rosé String Quartet</ref>) and Rosa Buxbaum.
          Nothing further is know of his life.</p>

        <p>Their son was <ref cRef="entity-000618">Siegfried Fritz Müller</ref>, pupil of <ref
            cRef="entity-000632">Heinrich Schenker</ref> and subsequently professional pianist and
          conductor.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <head>Correspondence with Heinrich Schenker</head>
        <p>Two letters from Paul Müller to Heinrich Schenker are known to survive: OJ 12/58, [1]-[2]
          (1923).</p>
      </div>
